LVIV, Ukraine â€” Marina Levinchuk said she received an alarming text message from the local authorities in the besieged city of Mariupol several days ago, before she decided to flee. â€œIf somebody dies in your family,â€ she said, recalling the message in her own words, â€œjust put the body outside, cover it, tie up the hands and the legs and leave it outside.â€

